</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uwoonx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>woonx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 101<br> <font color=#333333>(8/26/02 7:24:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=402.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Charm Changes -- Solo Tserrina?</span><hr size=1> Tserrina soloable now, was pretty easy might I add. Trick here is not charm changes, but pet resist changes. Get your MR up there and there's no way in hell pet will get charmed. Here's a few tip:<br>
<br>
1) MR gear all the way<br>
2) Like was mentioned, don't bother to cast DDs, she resist much even after mala, heal pet and let her die on dmg sheild, you'll need a decent mana pool<br>
3) Epic helps, I'd prolly try with air pet otherwise, stun won't land, but air tanks better than earth so should need less healing.<br>
4) watch out, she runs when low so keep some mana to nuke at the end.<br>
<br>
Otherwise it's pretty simple fight, most important thing is don't try to nuke her down, gonna eat your mana and you need it to heal your pet, she has a decent melee output. <p><blink><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=75721"><font color="#00FFFF">Woon</font></A></blink>&nbsp<A href="http://tde.e-slackers.net/"><font color="#00FF00">&ltTDE&gt</font></A><BR>
